<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-logo">
      <img src="/gitplum-logo.svg" alt="Gitplum" width="166" height="64" />
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge">
      <span class="badge-pulse"></span>
      Gitplum is currently in deep-indexing mode. Launching 2026.
    </div>
    <h1>The Knowledge Base<br />for <span>Software.</span></h1>
    <p>Gitplum transforms how coding agents discover, understand, and share software knowledge. Real-time intelligence for the world's code.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a href="#preview" class="btn btn-outline btn-large">See How It Works</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hero-terminal fade-in">
    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-header">
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        <span class="terminal-title">agent-context — gitplum</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body">
        <span class="t-muted">$</span> <span class="t-cmd">gitplum ask</span> vercel/next.js<br />
        <span class="t-white">"How does the App Router resolve parallel routes</span><br />
        <span class="t-white">&nbsp;when a layout has both @modal and @sidebar slots</span><br />
        <span class="t-white">&nbsp;with conflicting loading states?"</span><br /><br />
        <span class="t-muted">[resolving]</span> Analyzing vercel/next.js routing internals...<br />
        <span class="t-muted">[source]</span> <span class="t-plum">packages/next/src/server/app-render/walk-tree-with-flush.tsx</span><br />
        <span class="t-muted">[source]</span> <span class="t-plum">packages/next/src/server/app-render/create-component-tree.tsx</span><br /><br />
        <span class="t-green">&#10003;</span> <span class="t-white">Parallel routes resolve independently. Each slot renders</span><br />
        <span class="t-white">&nbsp;&nbsp;its own loading.tsx boundary. Conflicts are handled by the</span><br />
        <span class="t-white">&nbsp;&nbsp;innermost layout — @modal takes precedence only when its</span><br />
        <span class="t-white">&nbsp;&nbsp;route segment matches. See walk-tree-with-flush.tsx:142.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 160px 24px 80px;
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--white) 0%, var(--surface-alt) 100%);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: -200px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 800px;
    height: 800px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--plum-glow) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    margin: 0 auto 28px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 6px 18px;
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--plum);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .badge-pulse {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--plum-light);
    animation: pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0.4; }
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.25rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  h1 span {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--plum) 0%, var(--plum-light) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .hero p {
    font-size: 1.188rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto 40px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 16px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 72px;
  }

  .hero-terminal {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .t-cmd { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
  .t-flag { color: #93C5FD; }
  .t-plum { color: #C084FC; }
  .t-green { color: #4ADE80; }
  .t-white { color: #E4E4E7; }
  .t-muted { color: #52525B; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 130px 20px 60px;
    }

    .hero p {
      font-size: 1.063rem;
    }

    .hero-actions {
      margin-bottom: 48px;
    }
  }
</style>
